  "text": "More than half of the cases of postpartum headaches are benign [CITATION_1] . The most common cause of benign headaches is a post-dural puncture headache followed by primary headache syndromes (migraine, cluster, and tension headaches) as the second most common cause [CITATION_2] . On the other hand, life-threatening headaches are secondary headaches and are caused by complications of anesthesia, intracranial pathology, or pregnancy/delivery [15] . These include intracranial mass, preeclampsia, meningitis, strokes, venous sinus thrombosis, and reversible cerebral vasoconstrictive syndromes [15] .",
